North America
---
[1] United States (California, Solano County)
Date: Fri 7 Feb 2020
Source: KRON4 [abridged, edited]
https://www.kron4.com/news/bay-area/measles-case-confirmed-in-young-resident-in-solano-county/


Solano County Public Health is investigating a case of the measles, health officials confirmed Friday [7 Feb 2020]. The patient is a "young" resident of Solano County.

Health officials are now coordinating with places where exposures may have occurred along with notifying those who may have been exposed to the infection. The city where the individual lives has not been disclosed.

There were 1282 cases of the measles in the US in 2019 across 31 states. This year [2020], the US has seen a total of 5 cases, the CDC reports.

[Byline: Kayla Galloway]

