[2] United States (California, Los Angeles County)
Date: Fri 7 Feb 2020
Source: ABC7 [abridged, edited]
https://abc7.com/amp/5906348/


A local outbreak of measles among 5 people was confirmed Wednesday [5 Feb 2020] by the Los Angeles County Department of Public Health, which released a lengthy list of places where the public was possibly exposed to the virus.

The new outbreak includes 4 residents of the county who were exposed to a person described by the health department as an "unimmunized, international visitor who was infectious with the measles" while in L.A. County. [See URL for locations.]

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[See also https://www.precisionvaccinations.com/most-measles-cases-usa-are-related-international-travelers:

The Los Angeles County Department of Public Health (Public Health) confirmed a measles outbreak among 5 persons.

According to an LA Public Health press release issued on 5 Feb 2020, this measles outbreak began when a measles virus infectious international visitor was visiting the greater Los Angeles area. Furthermore, Public Health says, "additional measles cases may occur in LA County."

According to Public Health, during 2019, "there were 20 measles cases among LA County residents, in addition to 14 non-resident measles cases that traveled through LA County. Most of those individuals were not immunized or did not know whether they had ever been immunized or previously infected with the measles virus."

Eight of the measles outbreaks in the USA during 2019 occurred in under-immunized, close-knit communities.

During 2019, the CDC confirmed 1282 individual cases of measles in 31 states. About 73% of the cases were linked to recent measles outbreaks in New York City and Rockland County, NY.

